Class Pair<First,Second>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nanofi.net.primitive.Pair<First,Second>
  • Type Parameters:
    First - First value type
    Second - Second value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map.Entry<First,Second>

    public class Pair<First,Second>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map.Entry<First,Second>
    Pair class has ability of hold two type values.

    Make pair instance can from helper methods belows: 

     Pair<> pair = Pair.create(10, "Test"); // Return Pair<Integer, String> instance.

    Author:
    Kazuto Fukuchi
